    "The distribution for each method is then approximated by a histogram:P (∆ i) = #(samples∈∆i) #samples.",
    "We denote these binned empirical distributions as P MC for Monte Carlo and P S for our method, and the TV distance between these two distributions is then numerically computed by dTV(P MC, P S) = i P MC (∆i) -P S (∆i).Example 1 (1D Jump-diffusion with finite jump activity).",
    "To test the efficiency of our proposed method, we consider the following one-dimensional SDE: which has been applied in [9] to model CO 2 emissions and fuel-switching strategies.In this example, we set κ = 1, η = 1, and σ = 2.",
